original: Lyth, Åke Brunow, försäkringsdirektör, Jönköping, f. 29/12/04 i StMm av kont:chef Axel L. o. Marie-Louise Nylund. G. 30 m. Maj Lundberg. Barn: Margareta f. 31, Ingegerd 33, Birgitta 37, Anders 43. ~ Stud:ex. 24. DHS 29, stud. i Engl. o. Tyskl. 25-26. Tj :man i Försäkr. A-B Freja 29, För-säkr. A-B Norrl. 30-36, Thulebolagen 36-38, avd:chef i Försäkr :bol. Allm. Brand 38 dess verkst. dir. sed. 42, tillika verkst. dir. i Försäkr :bol. Hero 47. Styr:led. i Försäkr :bol. Aequitas, Valand o. Amphion, Stift. Anna Kjellbergs minne m. fl., v. ordf. i A-B Smål. Banks lokalstyr. i Jönköp.
translated: Lyth, Åke Brunow, insurance director, Jönköping, born on December 29, 1904 in StMm to managing director Axel L. and Marie-Louise Nylund. Married in 1930 to Maj Lundberg. Children: Margareta born in 1931, Ingegerd in 1933, Birgitta in 1937, Anders in 1943. Graduated from high school in 1924. Attended DHS (unknown abbreviation) in 1929, studied English and German from 1925-1926. Employed as a clerk in Insurance Company Freja in 1929, Insurance Company Norrland from 1930-1936, Thule Companies from 1936-1938, department manager in Insurance Company Allmänna Brand from 1938 and its managing director since 1942, also managing director in Insurance Company Hero from 1947. Board member of Insurance Companies Aequitas, Valand and Amphion, Anna Kjellberg Foundation and others, vice chairman of local board of Smålands Bank in Jönköping.
